# InvestTrack Project Rules

## Core Principles
• Never lie, be brutally honest.
• Code organization matters. Every class must have its own dedicated file (exceptions: State class of a StatefulWidget and enum-like classes such as Bloc events/states).

## Flutter & Bloc
• Use **Bloc**, NEVER use Cubit.
• Never use helper methods that return widgets (e.g., `Widget _buildItem()`). Create a dedicated widget class instead.
• For Row and Column, do not insert multiple `SizedBox` widgets for spacing. Use the `spacing:` property instead.
• Do not use full-screen loading indicators (`CircularProgressIndicator`) for short delays. Use subtle loading indicators integrated into the existing UI.

    - No hardcoded colors

## Styling & UI
• Never use hardcoded font sizes (e.g., `fontSize: 28`). Use values from `textTheme` (e.g., `textTheme.titleLarge?.fontSize`).
• Avoid hardcoded UI colors and text styles unless absolutely necessary.
• Prefer concise and elegant UI transitions.

## Code Quality & Types
• Always specify types explicitly.
• Prefer `Object?` over `dynamic`.
• Prefer `.firstOrNull` over `.first`.
• Do not use `Key? key`. Use `super.key`.
• **Nullable Handling**: Never use `!`. Use nullable handling (`?`) or assign to a local variable and check for null.
• **Type Casting**: Never use `as`. If unavoidable, guard it properly:
  ```dart
  if (value is SomeType) {
    final SomeType typedValue = value;
  }
  ```
• **Logic Structure**: Prefer explicit `else` blocks. Instead of guard clauses with early returns for negative conditions, use positive conditions with an explicit `else`.
  Example:
  ```dart
  // Prefer this:
  if (isConditionMet) {
    // logic
  } else {
    return null;
  }

  // Over this:
  if (!isConditionMet) {
    return null;
  }
  // logic
  ```

## Member Ordering
• Sort members of the class in an order that makes sense.
• `dispose` comes after `build`, so it should NEVER be placed before `build`.
